article.headline: Sam Houston St. 66, SE Louisiana 62 (OT)
article.story: HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- Shamir McDaniel hit a three-point play with 16 seconds left in overtime Thursday night to help Sam Houston State defeat Southeastern Louisiana 66-62. McDaniel's layup and free throw broke a 61-61 tie to give Sam Houston State a 64-61 lead. Southeastern Louisiana never led in overtime. Sam Houston's Reggie Rawlins forced the game into overtime when he hit a free throw with 19 seconds to tie the game at 56. He missed the second end of the one-and-one. Chris Jordan missed a field goal at the buzzer for the Lumberjacks. Ryan Bright came off the bench to lead Sam Houston (16-6, 7-3 Southland) with 13 points and eight rebounds. JeJuan Plair added 10 points. Ricky Woods led Southeastern Louisiana (11-11, 5-6) with 17 points and 18 rebounds. Chris Lee added 12 points and Joseph Polite had 10.
